d provide code for researchers to adapt to their own datasets. Our workflow focuses on measuring the morphology of cetaceans but is adaptable to other taxa. Our goal is for this open-source workflow to be accessible and accommodating to research projects across a range of budgets and to facilitate collaborations and longitudinal data comparisons. This workflow serves as a guide that is easily adoptable and adaptable by researchers to fit various data and analysis needs, and emergent technology and tools.},
